house of Eli the priest (1 Samuel 3) is of great vividness and has moved countless generations. In England and America the name was particularly popular among the 16th-century Puritans and among Nonconformists from the 17th to the 19th century. It became fashionable again in the 1990s."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Samuel Oxford was born in 1500, in Bratton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Samuel Oxford, was 25 and his mother, Bathsheba, was 20. He married Bathsheba Barrett about 1515, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1518, in his hometown."},"et":{"1500–after 1518":"1500–pärast 1518","1500–1518":"1500–1518","1501–Female":"1501–Surnud","1518–1588":"1518–1588","1475–1551":"1475–1551","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1588":"1588","1475":"1475","after 1518":"pärast 1518","1551":"1551","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","Abt 1515":"umbes 1515","of, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bratton, Wiltshire, England":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bratton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–after 1518":"1500–1518 jälkeen","1500–1518":"1500–1518","1501–Female":"1501–Kuollut","1518–1588":"1518–1588","1475–1551":"1475–1551","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1588":"1588","1475":"1475","after 1518":"1518 jälkeen","1551":"1551","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","Abt 1515":"noin 1515","of, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bratton, Wiltshire, England":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bratton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1500–after 1518":"1500–après 1518","1500–1518":"1500–1518","1501–Female":"1501–Décédée","1518–1588":"1518–1588","1475–1551":"1475–1551","1480–Female":"1480–Décédée","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1588":"1588","1475":"